text: Elizabeth Lynne Cheney (; born July 28, 1966) is an American attorney and politician. She was the U.S. Representative for from 2017 to 2023. Cheney was the House Republican Conference Chair, the third-highest position in GOP House leadership. She was removed from the position by a voice vote of the House Republican Conference on May 12, 2021 because she supported the second impeachment of Donald Trump and for not supporting Trump's efforts to overturn the results of the 2020 election. She is a neoconservative. Cheney is the elder daughter of former Vice President Dick Cheney and Lynne Cheney. On August 16, 2022, Cheney lost renomination in Wyoming's Republican primary to Trump-supported Harriet Hageman.Wyoming and Alaska primaries ==References== Category:1966 births Category:Living people Category:United States representatives from Wyoming Category:Politicians from Madison, Wisconsin Category:Republican Party (United States) politicians Category:Neoconservatives
